<%= render 'shared/side-nav' %>

<div class="container-decidesk">

  <div class="show-report-title">
      <h1 class="main-title text-left"><strong class="highlight">Report Analysis</strong></h1>
  </div>

  <div class="report-info">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <p>Name of the report : <strong><%= @report.name %></strong> </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <p>From <strong><%= @report.lines.first.ecriture_date.strftime("%d %B %Y") %></strong> to<strong> <%= @report.lines.treasury_last_day.ecriture_date.strftime("%d %B %Y")%></strong> </p>
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="cards-page-show">
          <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">

            <div class="col text-center">
              <h4 class="text-center"> Total <strong class="text-info">Treasury</strong>
              <%= link_to report_treasury_path(@report) do %>
                <i class="fas fa-search search" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="See more"></i>
              <% end %>
              </h4>
              <h1 class="text-center"><strong class="text-info"><%= number_with_delimiter(@treasury_balance.to_i, :delimiter => ',') %> â‚¬ </strong></h1>
            </div>
  
            <div class="col text-center">
              <h4 class="text-center">Total <strong class="highlight">Sales</strong>
              <%= link_to report_sales_path(@report) do %>
                <i class="fas fa-search search" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="See more"></i>
              <% end %>
              </h4>            
              <h1 class="text-center"> <strong class="highlight"><%= number_with_delimiter(@total_sales.to_i, :delimiter => ',') %> â‚¬ </strong></h1>
            </div>          
  
            <div class="col text-center mb-4">
              <h4 class="text-center">Total <strong class="text-primary">Expenditures</strong>
              <%= link_to report_expenditures_path(@report) do %>
                <i class="fas fa-search search" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="top" title="See more"></i>
              <% end %>
              </h4>                 
              <h1 class="text-center"> <strong class="text-primary"> <%= number_with_delimiter(@total_expenditures.to_i, :delimiter => ',') %> â‚¬ </strong></h1>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12 mt-3">
      <div class="card-page">
        <div class="ratio-card text-center">
                <h3 class="ratio-title">Margin</h3>
                <% if @margin > 0 %>
                  <h2 class="text-success font-weight-bold mb-4"><%= number_to_percentage(@margin, precision: 2) %></h2>
                  <p>This ratio shows the ability of your business to generate profits. It's positive here ðŸ¥³ Keep it up !</p>                               
                <% else %>
                  <h2 class="text-danger font-weight-bold mb-4"><%= number_to_percentage(@margin, precision: 2) %></h2>
                  <p>This ratio shows the ability of your business to generate profits. It's below O here ðŸ˜¢ You should conduct a cost analysis and take action to improve your profitability !</p>                                
                <% end %>
        </div>

        <div class="ratio-card text-center border-ratio">
                <h3 class="ratio-title">Cash to expenditures</h3>
                <% if @cash_ratio > 0 %>
                  <h2 class="text-success font-weight-bold mb-4"><%= number_to_percentage(@cash_ratio, precision: 2) %></h2>
                  <p>This ratio indicates your ability to pay expenditures with the existing cash ! It's above 0 so it's good news ðŸ¥³ Keep it up!</p>
                <% else %>
                  <h2 class="text-danger font-weight-bold mb-4"><%= number_to_percentage(@cash_ratio, precision: 2) %></h2>
                  <p>This ratio indicates your ability to pay expenditures with the existing cash ! It's below 0 ðŸ˜¢ You have to make sure you have enough cash to run the business and pay all expenditures !</p>                
                <% end %>
        </div>

        <div class="ratio-card text-center">
                <h3 class="ratio-title">Cash to sales</h3>
                <% if @sales_ratio > 0 %>
                  <h2 class="text-success font-weight-bold mb-4"><%= number_to_percentage(@sales_ratio, precision: 2) %></h2>
                  <p>This ratio indicates your ability to pay expenditures with the existing cash ! It's below 0 ðŸ˜¢ You have to make sure you have enough cash to run the business and pay all expenditures !</p>                                
                <% else %>
                  <h2 class="text-danger font-weight-bold mb-4"><%= number_to_percentage(@sales_ratio, precision: 2) %></h2>
                  <p>This ratio show the amount of cash generated by sales (vs. cash investments). It's negative so you most of your cash is genarated by investment ðŸ˜¢ This investment will hopefully generated more sales and contribute to your cash level in the future !</p>                
                <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>  
    </div>  
  </div>
</div> 